parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate speedometer can lead to speeding tickets, accidents, or loss of control, as the driver may not be aware of their actual speed.
symptoms: The speedometer displays incorrect speed readings
sometimes showing correct speed and other times showing obviously incorrect speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended opening of the power sliding door while the vehicle is in motion can cause occupants to fall out of the vehicle, leading to serious injury or fatality. Additionally, it can distract the driver and cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power sliding door opens without warning
the door chime alarm sounds while driving
the door appears to be locked but suddenly opens
the door does not respond to unlock commands.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Power Sliding Door Lock Mechanism
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty power sliding door lock mechanism can cause the door to open unintentionally, leading to occupant ejection or distraction of the driver, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power sliding door appears to be locked but does not respond to unlock commands
the door lock mechanism makes a clicking sound as if it is locking and unlocking
the door does not open when commanded.
